Job Description:
Job Title: * Senior Systems Analyst - TBFM
Location: *Washington, DC *Position: * Full-Time
Job Description: *Capital Group is seeking a Senior Systems Analyst to provide technical, engineering analytical, and planning support to the Time Based Flow Management (TBFM) Program Office. Specific responsibilities may include:
Perform task and information analyses to understand the human factors impact of new concepts of ATC and Technical Operations in the NextGen En Route programs;
Investigate user concepts, including Computer Human Interface (CHI) alternatives, fast time simulations, and HITL simulation demonstrations;
Provide concept alternatives for screen designs and navigation sequences, which may include relatively low-fidelity or high-fidelity products whose purpose is to provide alternatives that illustrate design and recommended CHI changes;
Research proof-of-concepts to validate future CHI options;
Collect, process, synthesize, and aggregate data to prepare and present human factors reports, briefings, position papers, databases, and other human factors documentation;
Provide operational CHI flexibility and commonality analysis alternatives;
Participate in quantitative analysis using operations research tools, economics, and other quantitative techniques in the areas of procedural implementations, performance issues, and contract compliance monitoring;
Contribute to the analysis, development, and drafting of Concept Requirements Definition documentation to include solution concept of operations, preliminary program requirements document, enterprise architecture products, realistic alternatives and rough cost and benefits estimates, detailed shortfall and functional analysis, safety risk assessment, ACAT designation request, and initial investment analysis plan;
Support the development of an Alternatives Risk Analyses;
Coordinate with site leads at each FAA facility that is scheduled to receive resources for site surveys and request site layouts and blueprints prior to site visit;
Prepare pre-site survey briefings to capture information pertinent to the activities at each site that a Site Survey Team is visiting;
Participate in pre-site visit meetings with the FAA installation team to plan personnel assignments for each of the scheduled site installation visits;
Prepare site in-briefs that include an agenda, description of the work activities to perform, goals and expectations, and descriptions/performance features of resources;
Perform site survey activities in equipment room racks and Airport Traffic Control Towers (ATCTs) to collect locations, measurements, electric power provisions, distances, equipment serial and part numbers, quantities of equipment, and other data necessary to ensure a successful installation;
Prepare site survey out-briefs, providing the FAA Site Lead with a draft of the action items to perform by the site, engineering services, the installation contractor, and the FAA prior to the scheduled installation date;
Prepare and deliver Facility Implementation Team (FIT) briefings;
Create updated FIT CD-ROMs containing materials to support sites in deploying TBFM;
Collaborate with site personnel to develop test agreements and operating procedures for Adjacent Center Metering (ACM);
Develop operational concepts of use on the deployment of TBFM as needed for sites;
Track ongoing site-generated problem reports and vendor-generated problem reports and ensure resolution;
Support the creation and documentation of sustainment processes, including site report processing, adaptation generation, and facilitating emergency releases of software;
Support operational evaluations to identify and track issues and make recommendations for operational improvements;
Provide recommendation on vendor-proposed resolution(s) to reported problems;
Participate in design reviews and make recommendations for sustainment strategies;
Provide Subject Matter Expertise at operational evaluations of new sustainment releases prior to deployment; and
Evaluate program release content, assess problem resolution effectiveness, and report any findings/issues to FAA leads.
Required Qualifications: *
Bachelor’s Degree in engineering, math, or science, or related field.
Eight (8) or more years of relevant experience (Senior I).
Fifteen (15) or more years of relevant experience (Senior II).
Must be a US citizen and meet eligibility requirements for a US Public Trust.
Candidate must demonstrate excellent oral and written communication skills; strong financial, analytical, and problem-solving skills; proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite (i.e., Word, Excel, PowerPoint); capacity to adapt to a fast-paced, dynamic environment; and the ability to work well on a team.
Preferred Qualifications: *
Master’s in in engineering, math, or science, or related field.
FAA systems engineering experience
Experience and knowledge of Time Based Flow Management
Familiarity with FAA Acquisition Management System (AMS) and Systems Engineering Manual
